0.15	14 March 2010
	- re-integrated into Package::Transporter
	- separated register_rule in register_potential and register_drain
	- replaced wild card symbols with text

0.14	13 March 2010
	- removed many temporary closures
	- integrated the concept of constant functions from Package::Transporter

0.13	11 March 2010
	- example how to trigger a 'use MODULE' in Suggested_Use.pm
	- default generator objects are now based on arrays

0.12	11 March 2010
	- cosmetic changes to the documentation
	- mentions MRO::Compat as an option for older versions of Perl

0.11	10 March 2010
	- unified error message upon failure; resembles Perl's
	- failure function in Generator class

0.10	09 March 2010
	- support for prototypes (useless unless honoured by AUTOLOAD)
	- more documentation

0.09	08 March 2010
	- ready-made matcher subroutines can be passed to register_potential
	- example generator to AUTOLOAD from a SQL database
	- separate pod files for rules and generators

0.08	07 March 2010
	- stuff it with convenience until it goes boom ;)
	- Generators as a separate class

0.07	06 March 2010
	- search path as separate class
	- updated README
	- completed Changes

0.06	05 March 2010
	- convenience function accepts arrays of names
	- added examples
	- load potentially_(can|defined) on demand
	- convenience method for export

0.05	04 March 2010
	- introduced symbolic wildcards (replaces two separate rule trees)
	- restored ISA search for potentially_can
	- added more tests

0.04	02 March 2010
	- changed implementation to be less than Package::Transporter

0.03	27 February 2010
	- made convenience generator more obvious

0.02	27 February 2010
	- changed to an interface like in Package::Transporter

0.01	24 February 2010
	- initial release to implement IMP_ON_DEMAND in Package::Transporter
